    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to Bratislava Town Council (Augsburg, 29 May 1548) </head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p>Gergely Bornemisza will recount quite a few things to them, they should
                            welcome him and do what he asks them in his name.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p>Prudentes et Circumspecti Domini et Amici Honorandissimi, salutem et
                    nostri commendationem!</p>
                <p>Referet vel nuntiabit nonnulla Dominationibus Vestris nomine nostro egregius
                    dominus <persName>Gregorius Bornemyza</persName><note type="critic">Gergely
                        Bornemisza. According this letter, he sent Gergely Bornemisza, but that is
                        likely to have been a mistake, and he was talking about Pál Bornemisza, see
                        Ep. 685.</note><ref>/o:olahus.tei.15480602_1</ref> aulicus regius. Rogamus
                    igitur Dominationes Vestras, velint amicitiae nostrae intuitu ea perficere, ad
                    quae praefatus Bornemyza easdem nomine nostro rogaverit et hortabitur, ut
                    gratias eisdem coram habere et referre possimus.</p>
                <p>Dominationes Vestrae bene valeant.</p>
                <p>Ex <placeName>Augusta Vindelicorum</placeName> 29. Maii 1548.</p>
                <p>
                    <seg type="signature">
                        <add corresp="Olahus" type="insert">Nicolaus Olahus episcopus Zagrabiensis
                            cancellarius regiae maiestatis etc. manu propria</add>
                    </seg>
                </p>
                <pb/>
            </div>
            <div style="handwritten" type="verso">
                <head>On the outer side:</head>
                <p>Prudentibus et circumspectis domino magistro civium iudici et iuratis civibus
                    civitatis Posoniensis dominis et amicis nobis honorandissimis.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
